===========================================================<br>
<br>
We the Aegis Wolves as family and friends seek to make time on line as enjoyable and entertaining as possible for everyone online.  In order to establish this goal and to become a more honorable and respected guild, we realize that a certain basic vision needs to be established for basic conduct, belief, and purpose.  We have come together as pack and guild because we share this vision for what we feel to be online utopia.  For this purpose we have composed the following articles to describe our beliefs and establish a basic code of conduct and organization to make our pack stand proud and honorable amongst the guilds of norrath and the lands beyond.  <br>
<br>
Charter: E Pluribus Unum.  <br>
<br>
Article I:<br>
Respect of the pack and the online community.   Membership as an Aegis wolf is second only to real life and loved ones in danger.  Personal honor, pride, vengeance and beliefs are secondary to your devotion to the guild and your pack mates.   You have the right to have these feelings and to voice them, but your loyalty to the pack is first and foremost.  Once a member of the wolves you have accepted full responsibility for representing the guilds honor in all situations and to look after the interests of our guild.  You will uphold the decision and stance of the guild one any subject online.  We are many wolves but we are one pack.   <br>
<br>
Article II:<br>
Discrimination is not an option.  The Aegis wolves do not and will not discriminate any player on any grounds.  Each player is entitled to there own individual opinions, belief and religion.  Players of all backgrounds, cultures, races, sexes, ages and lifestyles are welcome with the Aegis wolves, both as members and fellow adventurers.   No wolf will be apart of or involve themselves with actions or groups that violate this article.   Any action in defiance of this article will result in disciplinary action up to being stripped of membership.<br>
<br>
Article III:<br>
Bring Honor to the pack.  All Members represent the guild at all times. This means that they must, to the best of their ability, to follow the guild’s charter.  Never do anything to bring dishonor on the guild. This will include, but not limited to, “kill stealing”, stealing from members, bug abusing, flaming, Item farming without sharing a spawn, corpse looting, spamming players and other miscellaneous inappropriate behavior or disrespect. These actions will not be tolerated could result in disciplinary action up to removal from the Aegis Wolves.<br>
<br>
Article IV:<br>
There are no secrets in the guild.  Secrets are evil things that promote mistrust and avoidance of issues.   If you can not say it or do it in front of another wolf, then you should not be doing it.  As a wolf you are always expected to speak your peace and give your opinion then resign to the decision of the pack.  All members are trusted members with there own beliefs but the decisions of the guild are for the good of the pack not the individual.  Not presenting a problem before the guild or anonymously to the officers is not a crime, but you are the only one to blame when the problem continues.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Article V:<br>
The Aegis Wolves are a role-playing guild. As such members of the Aegis Wolves should develop a character and must try to stay in character while playing.  Also As the guild grows role-playing scenarios may be created and role-playing events and games may be done between guilds.  It is not mandatory that you participate in role-playing but would be appreciated.  Also though the spirit of role-play might include character based conflicts, These are character based and not player.  Anything done in the spirit of role-playing should remain so and not violate article III.<br>
<br>
Article VI:<br>
Protect the pack.  You will protect and assist any wolf in distress to the best of your ability.  As a member of the wolves you have a blood oath to your brethren in the pack.  If in dire need of assistance from a class or level of character you can turn to another wolf and in return must offer the same selfless support to the other members.  This is a privilege and not to be abused, Wolves are only required to help other wolves in need not in greed.  You do not have the right to have people camp for you.  It is not frowned upon to camp for a friend but it is a choice not a requirement.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Article VII:<br>
All wolves will assist the pack in times of war. Guild wars can only be initiated by a 50% vote of the Elder Wolves Council. Once the Elders vote to begin such a war notice must be sent immediately to all members. All members must be notified at least 24 hours in advance.   There are two types of guild wars we recognize.  The first is a hunt.  This is a war for honor and justice to punish those who Harass or other wise aggresses on our pack.   The second is a Quest war.   This is used in role-playing scenarios.  This is a sparring war in which we fight only to 50% health.  The first below 50% should yield or flee.   If a bought should be fought to the death then it should be agreed upon before hand.  <br>
<br>
Article VIII:<br>
Contribute to the pack.  The guild will maintain holdings for the protection, empowerment and role-playing use.  These items will be kept on mules and can be checked out as needed through the treasurer.   To check items out you must be of wolf rank or greater.  These Items are for the guild and are not to be dropped, traded or sold.  These Items will also be used to reequip members that have lost their holdings due to bugs, theft or lost corpse.  If you leave you return any Items.  The only contribution required is from rank quests all others are voluntary and appreciated.<br>
<br>
<br>
Article IX:<br>
The Call of the wild will always be answered.  The Aegis wolves pack signal.  It is a howl on guild say.  It is given with important announcements and guild member successes.   Every wolf should have this hot keyed.  If this is seen every wolf online will respond ASAP and pay attention to guild say for a minute or to for any important information on the howl.<br>
<br>
<br>
Article X:<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Motto:  Mean well, Do well, Speak well<br>
<br>
This charter was made as a guideline for the moral code of a wolf.  We understand that some scenarios may bend or stretch the solidity of these basic truths.   For more detailed guide on rules and behavior that seem too complex to choose the right path refer to the Aegis wolves guidelines for an in-depth explanation.  <br>
