Aegis wolves Guidelines: We understand that there is always a gray area with rules sometimes.  Hopefully this more detailed account of rules and procedures will be helpful.  Most are just a recount of what we feel to be common sense.  Any conflicts with these feel free to discuss at meeting and with officers.  These are guidelines, which means in some situations there may need to be some weighting done, above all do the right thing.<br>
<br>
1)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Your first online duty is to your guild.  The only exceptions being loved ones in danger.  If your guild needs you or your pack mates are in distress, refer to rule 4 for more on this.  You should be willing to leave a group to help a wolf.  This devotion does not require supplying fellow wolves with weapons and armor, or you to go out of your way to buff them.  It does however mean you should be willing to donate time and items you don’t need to the guild for other wolves to use as needed.  It only makes the guild stronger.  We realize you have friends out side the guild, but we are family and if you are needed you will get to a safe point and take your leave.  If at any time you feel your devotion lies with others over the guild you will be sorely missed but you are free to leave just notify any officer and tell them why and return all guild items.<br>
<br>
2)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Your fellow wolves are your online family.  You are expected to support them at all times. If they are in dire need you are required to assist them and remember next time it may be you who needs help.  Do not abuse this privilege.  No members of the guild are required to camp items for you or buff another member.  If they are standing right next to you they should assist with binds and such but it is not required that they do so.  If your require a buff you should go to them for it and not expect them to come to you.  We do not frown upon twinking or helping others in the guild with leveling and buffs, but it is the choice of the giver not the receiver.  Members are required to help members in need, not members in greed.  Another topic to discuss is pack mate behavior. If you feel that a member has dishonored the and there actions inappropriate then you need to get a non partial witness to confirm it and screen shots then bring it up to an officer. If the member was out of line it will be dealt with promptly.  If it is determined that he was not out of line no one will be punished and the matter will be dropped.<br>
<br>
