<br>
5)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Secondary character has become an issue and the guild has decided on the following course of action.  We want our members to be able to experience other races and classes without being separated from the guild.  But also we don’t want an influx of some many new characters with new members that we loose control of the guild and who everybody is.  So currently allowed to those of wolf rank or greater only two characters. This is ruffly four or five month’s time. Guild characters are not counted in this such as mules.  Officers due to duties are allowed only one that can have officer powers.  If you have your maximums allowed and wish to add another then you must remove one from the guild we would like to allow exceptions for those amongst use that tire more easily of a limited number of characters.  But at the same time we do not want people joining with eight characters and not being able to establish them selves in the guild, or leaving and us having eight characters with guild tags on the drop list we have to chase down.  As well as not being able to track down who is who<br>
<br>
<br>
