Wolf = Full-fledged wolf.  Has responsibility of mentoring guild cubs they are assigned, may have some minimal miscellaneous future duties.   Will be promoted to Protector after 3 months time as wolf and having proven them selves to be a dedicated member and valued friend of the guild.  You will be given a task to complete and at its completion will be promoted.   Must be at least wolf rank or higher to become an officer or receive titles.  If you are pursuing an officer ship then you must be willing to donate online time to the guild.  As an officer you have to be one of the most dedicated members.  Possible willing to sacrifice small amounts of RL time to the guilds structure.  Wolfs are allowed two characters, not including work charaters such as mules. <br>
<br>
Protector = With obtaining of this rank and future ranks all duties of the previous ranks are to be met as well.  As a protector wolf you are expected to be an active member of the guild.   Mentor Cubs.  May be called upon for tasks at any time.  The protection and safety of the guild and its members is your first priority.  This is with all wolves but where as for you If a hot trot is called you are the start running before you even hear where, for you are a senior member.  Will be promoted to the rank of Lone wolf upon completing of the lone wolf quest.  As well as 3 months time service as a protector and must be at lease level 20 to start the lone wolf quest.  Must be at least a protector to draw from guild funds for skill raising.  <br>
<br>
Lone wolf = Lone wolf as his brethren the protector maintains all responsibilities of all his ranks since wolf.  This includes mentoring new members and breaking personal activity to support guild protection.   You are the strong arm of the wolves having completed the lone wolf quest on your own unaided.   Your only additional duty is you may be called upon to perform in guild based quests as NPC’s, or to assist officers.  You will be promoted to Dire wolf upon completion of 4 months in rank and a completion of the dire wolf quest and obtaining the level of 35. <br>
<br>
Dire wolf  = The Dire wolf is a wolf that has been an active wolf for 1 year.   And has complete the requirements of all other ranks.   He still has the duties and responsibilities of his previous ranks.   May be called upon by officers for assistance or advice.  The rank is recognition of the wolves’ devotion to the guild and to his fellow wolfs.  Once reaching the level of 40.  You may take the great wolf quest to be promoted to great wolf. As well as 5 months time as a dire wolf.  <br>
<br>
Great Wolf =This rank is in honor of your accomplishments both as a wolf and your character.  You are the greatest of your brethren.  You will assist the officers in meetings and on guild decisions.  Your first duty is to defend the guilds Pups.  Then all other duties from previous ranks apply.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Officer ranks: Officers are the Elders of the wolves.   These were the original 10 members.  As they leave new wolves are nominated by their brethren non-officers and then voted for by the officers to fill these slots.  You must be of at least wolf rank to become and officer.  And will be expected to assist the pack master with specific duties while online.  A few might even have some minor duties off line such as keeping track of a member list or updating the web page.   These are the wolf council their word is law for they are to work for the best of the guild and are trusted by svarinya to do so.  If some one questions there requests they better have a good reason.  All officers can have up to 7 extra characters because some characters may be needed for guild purposes.  But only one character will have officer powers.<br>
<br>
<br>
Den Watcher = Youngest of the officers, must have been a full-fledged wolf.  Your basic duty is overseeing the pack.  Making sure internal disputes are handled quickly fairly even if it is just to report it.  Any external fights also need to be noted and reported to a pack elder or higher.  If you are the only one available take measures to diffuse it by separating the parties in question.   All events reported to the pack master.  Should be reported to fellow officers if still occurring when you leave.  You are not expected to resolve issues do your best report everything.    Will be promoted to pack elder After Sufficient duty in this rank determined by the pack master.  Completion of the Elder quest,  <br>
<br>
Pack Elder = You are a guardian and a leader.   Your job is to protect the pack and its name.  This means from quarrels both internal and external.  Fights and arguments need to be diffused as quickly and as fairly as possible.   You have been given the trust of the pack master as with all officers you have all the duties assigned to your commission, as well as the standards placed upon any wolf.   At this point you may be assigned specific duties. <br>
<br>
Grand Elder = This is a senior officer and ha full jurisdiction limited only by the Pack master.  Can be looked upon to make as an assistant to the pack master and must be willing to donate time to assist the pack master in duties.  Some sacrifice is required as an officer this rank sacrifices the most for the good of the pack.  But this rank also holds the greatest respect.<br>
<br>
Umbra Wolf  = This is a once officer that retired or was forced to resign with the pack at one point, They are allowed to retain there commission on return as a officer.  However since there are only 10 active officers, they have no officer vote and are not granted with the powers empowered to the active officers.   There rank is a totem of respect and council and the equivalent of wolf rank.<br>
<br>
Pack Master = This is the Guild leader on the existing game and server.  Only one position available per server or game depending on the lowest break down.  Currently Svarinya holds it.  This person assigns duties to individual officers.  Is present at all guild meetings or councils.  Must approve all litter councils.  Their vote counts as 1 and 1/2 for tie breaking purposes.  This is a status all its own.   This person has all officer requirements as well.  Has the ability to give titles and rank.  Must ok any new additions to the guild before the nametag is given.  This person may allow a person to skip some rank requirements if they feel they deserve.  <br>
<br>
Grand pack master  =. Position to be held when the wolves branch to other servers or games.  This will be the leader of all packs between games and servers.  Responsible for maintaining the web pages for the guild and supervising the individual pack masters.  Must make appearances between servers to various meetings and ceremonies. <br>
<br>
<br>
Titles For wolves:<br>
<br>
Knight of the Wolf: Carries the title of Sir at formal functions such as councils and meetings.  These people have gone out of their way and risked great peril to assist guild members, guild allies or just other players multiple times. Shown great dedication or valor during a hot trot.  Their dedication has brought pride upon hem selves and brought honor to the guild.<br>
<br>
Lord or Lady of the Hunt: Have participated in a victorious slaying of a dragon or a god.   Then acted appropriately for their rank after the looting.  Whining does not bring honor to the guild.  Formal title is Lord or Lady Achieved 50th level.  Then donated to the guilds treasury an 50th lvl + artifact. To be used for role-playing purposes only.<br>
<br>
Barer of the Shield – The Pack masters personal Body guard.  During time of war will be right beside the Pack master at all times.    This requires a level of 30 minimum.  You are the pack master’s champion, The champion of the wolves.  Due to playing times and RL there may be up to three in the guild at any point in time.  These are generally taken from the pack masers closest non officer friends and confidants.<br>
<br>
<br>
Positions: These are positions held that are duty bound most are officer positions.  These each have an assigned task and more than one person can be responsible for each job.  Each position will require about 1-2 hours a week of guild duty time.  Not just playing.  <br>
<br>
Scribe: wolf that assists the lore master.  Recording logs of meeting as posting this and other events on the guild message board.<br>
<br>
Treasurer: Keeps track of the Mule inventories and allows distribution of this to wolves.  Also keeps track of the monetary funds for skill development within the guild.  This person(s) inventories the mules once every three months submits a revised inventory to the guild leader. They are also the sole person(s) responsible for tracking loaned items. 2 officers assigned<br>
<br>
Lore Master: Keeps recorded documents and is responsible for knowing guild procedures and policies.  This person tacks the updating of documents and sending them out to the guild.  This person is also consulted when rules or policies are being applied or questions. This person keeps track of the member list and Dates of promotion so the list is available as needed.  The may also be asked to track other documentation and track important notes from meetings.  1 officer assigned <br>
<br>
Den mother/father: This is the recruiting officer in charge of the recruits in Cub procedures.  They must be an officer rank and handle all incoming recruits.  They make sure all cub procedures are followed to the letter and completed following the guild recruitment policy.  3 officers will be assigned here.<br>
<br>
Viceroy of the pact: Title is Viceroy.  They act as liaison between guilds, they are our diplomat and represent us with the Tunare trade coalition and with other guild relations.  This person needs to keep the pack master abreast of all issues.   Delivers formal threats of war, peace treaties and alliances.  Is the voice of the guild to other guilds.  Second only to the pack master.  This is a very dignified position.   Eventually as the guild grows there may be an assistant who must be of protector rank or greater.   1 officer assigned<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Awards: These are badges and marks awarded to wolves for meritorious service, increased duty and sacrifice, acts of courage and valiant support of the guild.  <br>
<br>
Wound Badge: Purple shield awarded to those who have suffered severe deaths and loss in a guild war, or defending a guild member in a guild sponsored event or duel.<br>
<br>
Order of the valiant: Purple and black shield with red stars given when a guild member does something beyond the ordinary in game usually to assist another and putting them selves at either great risk or sacrificing game time to do it.<br>
<br>
Event Shield: Gold shield given after a member has developed and supervised no less than 5 in game guild events.  These can be role-playing or competition events.  <br>
<br>
Valor of the Pioneer: Blue shield with two silver keys.  Awarded to those that start new chapters of the wolves on different servers or games.<br>
<br>
Glory and Honor: Red shield with gold 5-point star Given to those who have been outstanding members of the guild and who have retired from the game.<br>
<br>
Colors of vigor: Yellow and Red checkered shield given for two years service with the guild.<br>
<br>
Colors of Vitality: Black and white checkered shield given for 5 years service with guild.<br>
<br>
Everquest badge: Blue shield with a vertical red stripe. Given for being part of an EQ guild <br>
<br>
Ashrons Call: White shield with a red lazenge. Given for being part of a AC guild<br>
<br>
Badge of Commission: Blue and white striped shield with a rampant lion.  Officers badge.<br>
